author: Inside Edition
description: Vincent Battiloro, 17, is accused of deliberately slamming his car into two best friends as they rode an e-bike. One of the girls had reportedly spurned his advances. According to court papers, police say a suspect was driving 70 mph when he plowed into Maria Niotis and Isabella Salas. Inside Edition found video of Battiloro, an online gamer, posted before the incident, saying he was pranking Niotis by sending a pizza to her house. She had reportedly filed for a restraining order against him.
title: 17-Year-Old Suspect In Hit & Run Murder Is Vincent Battiloro

author: Inside Edition
description: Sean "Diddy" Combs was convicted in July of transportation to engage in prostitution but found not guilty of more serious charges. At Friday’s sentencing hearing, the 55-year-old disgraced music tycoon appeared to be crying as his son Quincy said his father is totally transformed and will never jeopardize his freedom again. Comb's ex-girlfriend, Cassie Ventura wrote a letter to the judge supporting the prosecution's call for an 11-year prison sentence.
title: Emotional Scenes At Sean 'Diddy' Combs Sentencing Hearing

author: Inside Edition
description: Leland Vittert, anchor of "On Balance" on NewsNation, is revealing that he is autistic. Vittert. did not speak until he was 3. At age 5 he was referred for an evaluation. He was diagnosed with autism, but his dad wanted to keep the diagnosis private. Vittert says growing up, he had no friends. His dad quit his job to devote himself to his son's upbringing and teach him how to navigate life. This year he published his memoir, "Born Lucky."
title: NewsNation Anchor Leland Vittert Reveals He Has Autism

author: Inside Edition
description: Few things are more beautiful this time of year than fall foliage in Vermont. Mother Nature's palette of warm colors can be mesmerizing, but also maddening to some. Every year there are traffic backups in New England with cars cruising with passengers in search of a "wow" moment. Police in Woodstock, Vermont, have decided to close down a file-mile stretch of road to cut down on traffic chaos so that local residents can go about their lives.
title: Traffic Chaos As People Head to Vermont To See Beautiful Fall Foliage

author: Inside Edition
description: One man learned his image was plastered on a wanted poster offering a $20,000 reward to anyone who could identify him. He was accused of decapitating a sea lion. But, it never happened. Jason Bietz says it started when a stranger encountered him on a California beach. She suspected Bietz was cutting up a dead sea lion that was lying on the shore, a violation of state law. Bietz says he contacted authorities to clear his name, which they now have done.
title: Authorities clear Man Accused Of Decapitating Sea Lion On Beach

author: Inside Edition
description: To celebrate the midnight release of Taylor Swift’s new album, "The Life of a Showgirl," Tracy Panase is transforming the singer’s former childhood home into party central for Swifties.
title: A Look Inside Taylor Swift's Childhood Home #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A painting depicting life at sea is just as expansive as an ocean. It also has a long title to go with it: "The Grand Panorama Of A Whaling Voyage 'Round The World." Currently on display at the Minnesota Marine Art Museum, the 1,300 foot moving image is taller than the Empire State Building. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: This Painting Is Longer Than The Empire State Building

author: Inside Edition
description: In just 45 minutes, six homes collapsed, one after the other, from Mother Nature's fury.
title: Coastal Flooding Sweeps Away North Carolina Homes #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Ignoring a school bus's flashing lights and stop signs could land a driver a $1000 fine in Atlanta, where this video was taken. But how do you ticket a driverless car? Recently, cops in San Bruno, California, stopped an autonomous car that made an illegal U-turn. It's an issue states are grappling with as companies like Waymo put more of their vehicles on the roads. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Who Gets The Ticket When A Driverless Car Commits Traffic Violation?
